00:43.835 --> 00:45.337
This is how you'll do it.

00:45.378 --> 00:46.629
Oh, my God.

00:48.590 --> 00:49.758
Yeah!

00:51.593 --> 00:52.594
Uh, yeah.

00:52.635 --> 00:54.387
Oh, hi.

00:56.765 --> 00:58.725
Are you ready for
this wedding day?

00:58.767 --> 00:59.726
Oh, my God.

00:59.768 --> 01:02.562
Woo, we got married, bitches!

01:02.604 --> 01:06.399
So thankful.
Look at this rainbow!

01:06.441 --> 01:08.109
Yes!

01:17.160 --> 01:18.870
You kissed Mzi.

01:18.912 --> 01:20.830
We kissed last night.

01:20.872 --> 01:22.415
What, no,
we kissed last night.

01:25.377 --> 01:27.379
Boat romances...
they're dangerous.

01:30.382 --> 01:31.758
This is what happens
when I'm single.

01:31.800 --> 01:33.426
Woo!

01:33.468 --> 01:36.513
The lazy Susan
is being ridden hard.

01:40.308 --> 01:41.559
Come on.

01:41.601 --> 01:42.727
Whoa [bleep]!

01:42.769 --> 01:44.145
Oh, my God.

01:45.730 --> 01:47.148
Keep the line outta
the water, please.

01:47.190 --> 01:48.441
[bleep]

01:48.483 --> 01:50.402
To lead people
is to invest in them.

01:50.443 --> 01:51.569
-Amazing.
-Good job.

01:51.611 --> 01:52.779
-Thanks so much.
-You're welcome.

01:52.821 --> 01:54.322
It's up to you.

01:59.744 --> 02:01.246
Right now, I'm pissed off
with you.

02:01.287 --> 02:03.623
I don't care.
I'm, like, leaving

02:03.665 --> 02:05.583
Hey, Mom,
I'm quitting this boat.

02:05.625 --> 02:07.627
That's an incident
report, Malia.

02:07.669 --> 02:09.796
-I'm not a chief officer.
-I don't give a [bleep]!

02:09.838 --> 02:12.340
You should have come
to me that he was hurt.

02:12.382 --> 02:14.175
-[bleep]
-Ugh.

02:14.217 --> 02:15.969
His blood pressure's really
high, he has chest pains.

02:16.011 --> 02:17.470
He needs to go to the hospital.

02:17.512 --> 02:19.305
Red on deck, red on deck.

02:19.347 --> 02:21.599
This is gonna pass, I promise.

02:21.641 --> 02:23.309
Ah!

02:23.351 --> 02:26.563
If we're not challenged,
then we won't grow.

02:26.604 --> 02:27.939
Whoa, what's going on there?

02:27.981 --> 02:29.858
If you [bleep] up, it's on me!

02:29.899 --> 02:30.942
Everybody's being so
----ing dramatic!

02:30.984 --> 02:36.489
Stop the ----ing noise!

02:36.531 --> 02:38.700
Stop being a kiss-ass,
[bleep] off!

02:38.742 --> 02:40.243
Hey, whoa, enough!

02:40.285 --> 02:41.870
This is your chance
to redeem yourself.

02:41.911 --> 02:43.663
If you don't do it,

02:43.705 --> 02:45.373
then you're off the boat
at the end of this charter.

03:09.439 --> 03:11.524
Hello?

03:11.566 --> 03:13.443
-Hi!
-Hi!

03:13.485 --> 03:14.444
How are you?

03:14.486 --> 03:15.779
I'm good.

03:15.820 --> 03:16.780
-Welcome okay.
-I'm a hugger.

03:16.821 --> 03:17.781
Okay.

03:17.822 --> 03:19.282
I'm Katie.

03:19.324 --> 03:20.867
-Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you, too.

03:20.909 --> 03:22.660
Wow, I'm looking
forward to this.

03:22.702 --> 03:25.455
I mean, this is impressive.
You have some experience.

03:25.497 --> 03:26.873
Yeah.

03:26.915 --> 03:29.542
I don't consider myself
a typical chief stew.

03:29.584 --> 03:34.381
My last boat was a 73-meter, and
had about seven girls under me.

03:34.422 --> 03:36.299
When you're in a higher role,

03:36.341 --> 03:38.468
I think it's important to show
that you still work as hard.

03:38.510 --> 03:39.761
It's a Capricorn thing.

03:39.803 --> 03:41.429
I think you get more out of
your crew

03:41.471 --> 03:43.556
if you're trying to keep
a good vibe on board,

03:43.598 --> 03:44.891
as opposed to
if you're just a psycho bitch

03:44.933 --> 03:46.393
telling them what to do.

03:46.434 --> 03:47.560
They're gonna be
like [bleep] you.

03:47.602 --> 03:48.728
-Cool.
-Go check out your bunk.

03:48.770 --> 03:49.854
I'll go down to the crew mess...

03:49.896 --> 03:50.855
-Yeah.
-...and check that out.

03:50.897 --> 03:51.856
Yeah, all right, welcome aboard.

03:51.898 --> 03:53.692
Cool, thank you, Sandy.

03:53.733 --> 03:55.819
Last season was the hardest
season I ever did in my life.

03:55.860 --> 03:59.823
Everybody does this, they look
back and they have regrets

03:59.864 --> 04:02.033
on how they acted
or what they did.

04:02.075 --> 04:04.327
I was ready to go,
this is it,

04:04.369 --> 04:05.912
I don't want to
do this anymore.

04:05.954 --> 04:08.665
This is the stuff that
defines our character.

04:08.707 --> 04:11.376
Can we find it when
we're ready to give up?

04:11.418 --> 04:14.504
I come back because
I love to mentor people.

04:14.546 --> 04:16.589
and I wanna lead a team.

04:16.631 --> 04:17.757
That's why I'm here.

04:19.551 --> 04:20.844
Hello?

04:22.887 --> 04:25.432
-Sorry, I'm getting changed!
-Oh, no worries.

04:25.473 --> 04:27.434
-I'm Katie.
-Katie, Malia.

04:27.475 --> 04:28.810
-Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

04:28.852 --> 04:29.978
-Hi.
-Hi.

04:30.020 --> 04:31.771
-I'm Mathew.
-Hi, Mathew.

04:31.813 --> 04:33.398
-Nice to meet you.
-Welcome.

04:33.440 --> 04:34.399
Thank you very much.

04:34.441 --> 04:36.067
Are you the new chief stew?

04:36.109 --> 04:37.444
-Yes.
-Awesome, cool.

04:37.485 --> 04:38.445
-Yeah.
-Are you excited?

04:38.486 --> 04:40.321
A little nervous.

04:40.363 --> 04:41.489
I mean, we're here now, right?

04:41.531 --> 04:43.324
-Yeah.
-No turning back.

04:43.366 --> 04:44.451
-Let me show you your galley.
-Awesome, thank you so much.

04:44.492 --> 04:46.369
Welcome aboard.
Impressive.

04:46.411 --> 04:48.079
Like, you've worked
for some impressive people.

04:48.121 --> 04:51.124
Yeah. I've been a professional
chef for the last 14 years.

04:51.166 --> 04:53.376
I've been a private chef
for the Dolan family,

04:53.418 --> 04:55.086
who own Madison Square Garden,

04:55.128 --> 04:58.089
Rupert Murdoch, Hugh Jackman,
Robert Kraft.

04:58.131 --> 05:00.592
I'm always nervous when
I go into a new job.

05:00.633 --> 05:03.553
I wanna make everyone happy.
Just hope people like me.

05:03.595 --> 05:05.013
Looking forward
to the best season ever.

05:05.055 --> 05:06.139
Yeah, me too.

05:06.181 --> 05:07.557
-Oh, nice.
-Yeah.

05:07.599 --> 05:08.767
Not too bad.

05:08.808 --> 05:09.768
Good amount of work to do today.

05:09.809 --> 05:11.478
Yeah. Welcome aboard.

05:11.519 --> 05:13.021
Thank you so much.
I'm excited to work for you.

05:13.063 --> 05:14.356
-It's a pleasure to have you.
-Yeah, thanks.

05:14.397 --> 05:15.440
Awesome, I'll leave you to it.

05:21.154 --> 05:22.530
Hi!

05:22.572 --> 05:24.699
-How are you?
-Good, how are you?

05:24.741 --> 05:26.493
Good, what'd you do
over the past year?

05:26.534 --> 05:27.494
-Yeah.
-Yeah?

05:27.535 --> 05:28.912
I've been nonstop.

05:28.953 --> 05:30.830
Just got off a charter
season in the Med, so.

05:30.872 --> 05:32.040
Yeah? What size boat?

05:32.082 --> 05:34.834
A 55, second officer.

05:34.876 --> 05:36.086
Bosun, second officer,
so yeah.

05:36.127 --> 05:37.879
-Cool.
-Very good.

05:37.921 --> 05:40.507
It's actually a crazy feeling
being back in Croatia,

05:40.548 --> 05:43.510
because the last time I was
here, I was a green deckie.

05:43.551 --> 05:44.678
Practice.

05:44.719 --> 05:46.638
Go forward, go reverse.

05:46.680 --> 05:48.807
It was the opportunities
that Captain Sandy gave me

05:48.848 --> 05:51.393
my first season that made
me wanna stick with yachting.

05:51.434 --> 05:53.812
-Here's your deck crew.
-Okay.

05:53.853 --> 05:55.397
Deck, deck, engineer,
that's cool.

05:55.438 --> 05:57.190
Cool, thank you,
I'll look over these, yeah.

05:57.232 --> 05:58.525
Yeah, welcome back, Malia.

05:58.566 --> 05:59.693
-Thanks, appreciate it.
-Okay.

05:59.734 --> 06:01.027
-Hi!
-I'm Mathew.

06:01.069 --> 06:02.737
-I'm Katie.
-Nice to meet you, Katie.

06:02.779 --> 06:03.738
Yes.

06:03.780 --> 06:04.906
Awesome.

06:08.201 --> 06:09.744
Oh, hey.

06:09.786 --> 06:10.912
-David.
-David?

06:10.954 --> 06:11.913
-Malia.
-Nice to meet you.

06:11.955 --> 06:12.914
Nice to meet you.

06:12.956 --> 06:13.915
Sweet.

06:13.957 --> 06:15.542
What do I start with here?

06:15.583 --> 06:16.751
All right.

06:20.088 --> 06:21.089
Let's start this bad boy.

06:21.131 --> 06:22.549
-Yeah.
-I'm Lexi.

06:22.590 --> 06:23.883
-I'm Katie.
-Nice to meet you.

06:23.925 --> 06:24.968
Nice to meet you, too.

06:25.010 --> 06:26.136
I guess I'll be your stewardess.

06:26.177 --> 06:27.721
You will.

06:27.762 --> 06:29.514
I'll come down with you.

06:29.556 --> 06:31.016
How long have you been involved
in all this noise, then?

06:31.057 --> 06:32.559
Four years, I think.

06:32.600 --> 06:33.560
Yeah, same.

06:33.601 --> 06:34.644
Where are you from?

06:34.686 --> 06:35.979
I'm from Bahamas, Nassau.

06:36.021 --> 06:38.565
-Oh, beautiful.
-Yeah.

06:38.606 --> 06:42.068
I was Miss Bahamas 2013.
But I don't tell people.

06:42.110 --> 06:44.070
I did a Miss Bahamas pageant.

06:44.112 --> 06:46.948
-Wow.
-Especially yachties.

06:46.990 --> 06:48.533
Like, they find out
I was in a pageant,

06:48.575 --> 06:50.493
they're just like,
I'm your boss.

06:50.535 --> 06:53.788
Okay, I'll be the Cinderella
with the broom, that's fine.

06:53.830 --> 06:56.499
I'm still pretty; you're not.
So, it's okay.

06:59.169 --> 07:00.462
Hey there, I'm Lloyd.

07:00.503 --> 07:01.755
-Lloyd? Malia.
-Yeah.

07:01.796 --> 07:03.048
-Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

07:04.966 --> 07:06.926
We got sh-- to do.

07:06.968 --> 07:08.887
Cool, now there's three of us.

07:08.928 --> 07:10.472
On it.

07:10.513 --> 07:11.848
Possibly another Brit.

07:11.890 --> 07:13.016
Oh!

07:13.058 --> 07:14.934
My last boat is all British.

07:14.976 --> 07:16.770
Well, thankfully you already
know the British, so I'm fine.

07:16.811 --> 07:18.104
-Yeah.
-My ex-boyfriend's British.

07:18.146 --> 07:20.190
Oh, no, I'm sorry.

07:20.231 --> 07:23.276
The break-up with Tom
has really taken a toll on me.

07:23.318 --> 07:27.072
He was someone that
I thought was a forever.

07:27.113 --> 07:29.783
I thought I was in love.

07:29.824 --> 07:31.618
I just wanna put my head down
and work for a bit,

07:31.659 --> 07:32.911
and it's just that
tough period

07:32.952 --> 07:35.497
where you just gotta
figure sh-- out.

07:35.538 --> 07:36.956
But I will.

07:36.998 --> 07:39.000
That's yachting.

07:39.042 --> 07:40.001
-Hey, how's it going?
-Hello, buddy, I'm Lloyd.

07:40.043 --> 07:41.169
-Dave.
-Hey.

07:41.211 --> 07:42.295
-Nice to meet you.
-And you, fella.

07:42.337 --> 07:43.672
How do you say your name?

07:43.713 --> 07:44.673
-"Muzi."
-"Muzi."

07:44.714 --> 07:46.299
Yeah...

07:46.341 --> 07:47.300
And here's your bosun, Malia.

07:47.342 --> 07:48.677
-Hi, there.
-Hi!

07:48.718 --> 07:49.678
-Z.
-Z, Malia, nice to meet you.

07:49.719 --> 07:51.054
Nice to meet you.

07:51.096 --> 07:52.597
Z, whenever you're ready,
just get changed

07:52.639 --> 07:54.140
and me and the guys
are on the sundeck.

07:54.182 --> 07:55.725
-Awesome, lovely.
-Yeah.

07:55.767 --> 07:56.768
See you then.

08:20.333 --> 08:22.002
-I'm Katie. Oh sh--.
-Hi.

08:22.043 --> 08:24.129
-I'm Courtney, nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

08:24.170 --> 08:25.755
So, you're from the UK?

08:25.797 --> 08:27.090
Yes, from Wales.

08:27.132 --> 08:28.550
-Hey.
-How's it going?

08:28.591 --> 08:29.759
-Dave.
-Mzi, nice to meet you.

08:29.801 --> 08:30.760
-Nice to meet you.
-Hey, Z.

08:30.802 --> 08:32.137
Hey.

08:32.178 --> 08:33.221
Sorry our introduction
was brief, but...

08:37.392 --> 08:38.601
No worries.

08:38.643 --> 08:40.687
Yeah, it might get a little hot.

08:43.064 --> 08:45.066
Idiot.

08:45.108 --> 08:46.234
Wipe it gently.

08:46.276 --> 08:47.944
-Soap and water, right?
-Yeah.

08:47.986 --> 08:49.112
We're just starting
with the wash-down.

08:52.073 --> 08:54.034
Nice,
is this your first boat, or?

08:54.075 --> 08:55.702
First big boat.

08:55.744 --> 08:56.828
-Nice, okay, cool.
-Yeah.

08:58.830 --> 09:00.665
-Oh...
-But yeah, just...

09:00.707 --> 09:02.250
Sorry, I should have
gauged that better.

09:02.292 --> 09:03.918
I guess... yeah.

09:03.960 --> 09:05.837
I love the notebook.

09:05.879 --> 09:08.048
Like, I didn't realize
he was that green.

09:08.089 --> 09:11.718
This means I can teach him
like I was taught.

09:11.760 --> 09:13.053
We've just come
this full circle,

09:13.094 --> 09:14.971
so that's pretty special to me.

09:16.931 --> 09:18.224
<i>All crew, all crew.</i>

09:18.266 --> 09:19.726
Ow, [bleep].

09:19.768 --> 09:21.144
Please meet me
in the main salon.

09:21.186 --> 09:22.312
Copy.

09:22.354 --> 09:24.647
-Hi.
-Hi!

09:24.689 --> 09:25.690
-Hi, Courtney.
-Lexi, nice to meet you.

09:25.732 --> 09:26.733
Nice to meet you.

09:26.775 --> 09:27.984
What's up, man, I'm Mat.

09:28.026 --> 09:28.985
Yeah, Lloyd, nice
to meet you, man.

09:29.027 --> 09:29.986
Lloyd.

09:30.028 --> 09:31.237
All right, welcome.

09:31.279 --> 09:32.364
We're beginning
our charter season,

09:32.405 --> 09:33.740
I love your energy, it's up.

09:33.782 --> 09:35.241
If you want a career in this,

09:35.283 --> 09:37.744
and this is really,
truly your passion,

09:37.786 --> 09:39.788
I'm here to help
make that happen.

09:39.829 --> 09:42.707
We just wanna stay within
the guidelines of protocol.

09:42.749 --> 09:44.292
Injuries...

09:44.334 --> 09:46.294
if any guest or you guys
are injured in any way,

09:46.336 --> 09:47.962
I wanna be the first
to know about it.

09:48.004 --> 09:51.049
If any of you are
on any prescribed medication,

09:51.091 --> 09:52.717
we need to log it.

09:52.759 --> 09:55.845
So, no drugs, and
no drinking while on charter.

09:57.138 --> 09:58.765
Well, it's kinda funny.

09:58.807 --> 10:00.225
Alex is the chief engineer,

10:00.266 --> 10:01.351
Marten is the chief officer,

10:01.393 --> 10:03.269
and Jake is our second engineer.

10:03.311 --> 10:04.646
So, that's our team.

10:04.688 --> 10:06.231
Do you like the boat?

10:06.272 --> 10:07.273
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

10:07.315 --> 10:09.651
It reminds me of Titanic inside.

10:09.693 --> 10:10.819
Oh!

10:10.860 --> 10:12.028
You've been on the Titanic?

10:12.070 --> 10:13.363
-Yeah, all the time.
-How was it?

10:13.405 --> 10:15.407
Lady Michelle was
designed for charter.

10:15.448 --> 10:17.701
It's a solid vessel,
it's elegant.

10:17.742 --> 10:19.244
I like to say it's
sort of like Disneyworld...

10:19.285 --> 10:21.079
you never see them take
the garbage out.

10:21.121 --> 10:23.289
There's a lot of stairs on
the boat, so the crew

10:23.331 --> 10:26.292
can go through each deck without
being seen by the client.

10:26.334 --> 10:27.919
It's gonna be
a lot of work for them.

10:27.961 --> 10:29.170
Tomorrow, our charter starts,

10:29.212 --> 10:30.755
so let's get our
boat turned around

10:30.797 --> 10:31.923
and get ready for tomorrow.

10:31.965 --> 10:33.133
All right.

10:33.174 --> 10:34.300
-Sounds good.
-You're free!

10:34.342 --> 10:35.760
-Nice.
-Woo!

10:35.802 --> 10:37.137
Okay, let's do it,
girls, come on.

10:37.178 --> 10:39.806
So, let's start
with the house, and then...

10:39.848 --> 10:41.850
-Roger.
-Exterior, interior.

10:41.891 --> 10:43.143
We're gonna
jump straight into it.

10:43.184 --> 10:44.144
Okay, cool.

10:44.185 --> 10:45.395
The boat's quite dusty.

10:48.982 --> 10:50.817
Actually... [bleep].

10:50.859 --> 10:53.695
All crew, all crew, I believe
we have provisions on the dock.

10:55.196 --> 10:56.698
Oh, that's a big truck.

10:58.199 --> 10:59.909
That's a lot, huh?

10:59.951 --> 11:01.036
What is that?

11:02.996 --> 11:04.456
So, that whole truck full?

11:04.497 --> 11:07.292
Never really seen
anything like this.

11:07.334 --> 11:08.418
Of course it's a red flag.

11:12.213 --> 11:13.173
Coming up...

11:13.214 --> 11:15.884
That was terrible.

11:15.925 --> 11:17.344
I have failed them.

11:17.385 --> 11:19.512
-We're on a mega-yacht!
-I get it.

11:19.554 --> 11:21.056
-Sorry, I'm...
-We're on a mega-yacht!

11:26.061 --> 11:27.520
All crew, all crew, I believe
we have provisions on the dock.

11:29.272 --> 11:30.774
So, that whole truck full?

11:30.815 --> 11:32.025
Dear God.

11:34.861 --> 11:36.363
That's a lot, huh?

11:36.404 --> 11:38.865
I've never really seen
anything like this.

11:38.907 --> 11:40.367
What is that?

11:40.408 --> 11:41.868
I thought it was going to
be a sh-- show

11:41.910 --> 11:43.370
before the provisions arrived.

11:43.411 --> 11:45.288
As soon as I see these pallets,

11:45.330 --> 11:49.250
I've probably over-ordered
and [bleep] now I'm stressed.

11:49.292 --> 11:50.251
Now the fun starts.

11:50.293 --> 11:51.795
Oh, yeah.

11:54.130 --> 11:56.508
Sweet.

11:56.549 --> 11:57.801
Where do you want these to go?

11:57.842 --> 11:59.844
Straight into the main deck.

11:59.886 --> 12:01.471
Phew, saved!

12:03.848 --> 12:04.933
You know, it's the first order.

12:06.351 --> 12:07.602
Yeah.

12:07.644 --> 12:08.603
You don't need to go to
the gym, eh?

12:08.645 --> 12:10.021
No.

12:10.063 --> 12:11.022
I have some cling
film and stuff,

12:11.064 --> 12:12.023
do you reckon this is yours?

12:12.065 --> 12:13.817
I reckon it is.

12:13.858 --> 12:17.070
I first started yachting as,
like, a stewardess/nanny.

12:17.112 --> 12:19.197
Then I got a job on a 60-meter.

12:19.239 --> 12:21.991
That's where I became
the queen of laundry.

12:22.033 --> 12:23.118
Have you been on
a boat recently?

12:23.159 --> 12:25.120
