This is our bridge deck aft.

25:44.377 --> 25:46.212
This will be
the main dining area.

25:46.254 --> 25:48.131
Obviously, weather-dependent.

25:48.173 --> 25:50.175
We're from Texas,
we'll bring the sun.

25:50.216 --> 25:51.176
Chicken, chicken?

25:51.217 --> 25:52.761
Chicken and chickpea.

25:54.304 --> 25:55.347
Sundeck aft.

25:55.388 --> 25:56.806
There we go, there's the sun.

25:56.848 --> 25:58.683
-This, you just give it a stir.
-Okay.

25:58.725 --> 25:59.976
We've got another
dining as well.

26:00.018 --> 26:00.977
Amazing.

26:01.019 --> 26:02.312
We have a big-ass Jacuzzi.

26:02.354 --> 26:03.980
It's Texas-size.

26:04.022 --> 26:05.065
This plate?

26:05.106 --> 26:06.191
This is quinoa,
that is lentils.

26:06.232 --> 26:07.984
Okay.

26:08.026 --> 26:09.069
And then we'll come
through to the primary suite.

26:09.110 --> 26:10.445
Oh, boy.

26:10.487 --> 26:12.197
We have two bathrooms.

26:12.238 --> 26:13.740
-Terez.
-Girl!

26:13.782 --> 26:17.327
Woo, child, steamroll here.

26:17.369 --> 26:18.870
I mean, if you want,
you can all sleep in here.

26:18.912 --> 26:19.954
Yeah.

26:19.996 --> 26:21.748
Saves me getting
the cabins done.

26:21.790 --> 26:24.834
Ugh, come on, Mathew,
hang the [bleep] in there.

26:29.464 --> 26:31.007
Shorts, red shoes.

26:35.303 --> 26:36.429
She's like, "I've never
been through

26:36.471 --> 26:38.014
so many bottles
on a walkthrough."

26:38.056 --> 26:40.183
-Well...
-I'm into it.

26:40.225 --> 26:42.394
If this was me,
I'd be doing the same thing.

26:42.435 --> 26:45.230
Then we come down
to the lower guest area.

26:46.773 --> 26:48.900
So we've got a twin
and then a double.

26:48.942 --> 26:50.276
I'm gonna nail my head
on these things.

26:50.318 --> 26:51.361
I know.

26:51.403 --> 26:53.738
This is Captain Sandy's haven.

26:53.780 --> 26:54.739
This is where the magic happens.

26:54.781 --> 26:56.074
-Yes, it is.
-Yay!

26:56.116 --> 26:57.992
-Since you're all in here...
-Yeah.

26:58.034 --> 26:59.202
I got some news to break to you.

26:59.244 --> 27:00.412
Our chef injured himself.

27:00.453 --> 27:04.082
Oh!

27:04.124 --> 27:06.251
We are leaving him at
the dock to go get an MRI.

27:06.292 --> 27:07.377
Oh, no!

27:07.419 --> 27:09.462
He did prepare a lunch

27:09.504 --> 27:12.340
that we're gonna try
to make it happen.

27:12.382 --> 27:14.050
-There will be no chef?
-No chef?

27:14.092 --> 27:15.218
Sorry.

27:15.260 --> 27:17.053
Oh, my God.

27:25.270 --> 27:26.187
-Since you're all in here...
-Yeah.

27:27.480 --> 27:28.606
I got some news
to break to you.

27:28.648 --> 27:29.983
Our chef injured himself.

27:30.025 --> 27:31.443
Oh!

27:31.484 --> 27:32.944
We are leaving him
at the dock to go get an MRI.

27:32.986 --> 27:34.279
Oh, no!

27:34.320 --> 27:36.281
-There will be no chef?
-No chef?

27:36.322 --> 27:38.158
Because of COVID,
our hands are tied.

27:38.199 --> 27:40.535
It isn't like I can
get another chef like that.

27:40.577 --> 27:42.829
You're gonna have to tip us,
if that's the case.

27:45.165 --> 27:47.167
In my entire career,
this has never happened to me.

27:47.208 --> 27:49.169
You know what,
we're gonna make it happen.

27:49.210 --> 27:50.170
-That's right, that's right.
-We're gonna make it happen.

27:50.211 --> 27:52.130
We could be ----ed.

27:52.172 --> 27:53.465
-Thank you, Sandy.
-Yeah, thank you.

27:53.506 --> 27:55.008
Cheers.

27:55.050 --> 27:56.092
So, coming off the
dock you're gonna

27:56.134 --> 27:57.260
be forward on the foredeck,

27:57.302 --> 27:58.887
you guys are gonna
be on the stern,

27:58.928 --> 28:00.305
so you can
start prepping your lines.

28:04.351 --> 28:06.019
Yeah, that's fine.

28:06.061 --> 28:07.020
All crew, all crew,
we're ready for departure.

28:07.062 --> 28:08.355
Copy.

28:08.396 --> 28:10.482
So, if we could do lunch,
I think, now,

28:10.523 --> 28:11.900
and then we want
to do water sports.

28:11.941 --> 28:12.901
Yeah.

28:12.942 --> 28:13.902
Okay, Malia, you ready?

28:13.943 --> 28:15.236
Captain Sandy, stand by.

28:15.278 --> 28:17.072
Oh sh--.

28:17.113 --> 28:18.448
They wanna go ahead
with lunch right away.

28:18.490 --> 28:20.158
Yep.

28:20.200 --> 28:21.159
Yeah.

28:21.201 --> 28:22.494
Yep.

28:22.535 --> 28:24.287
All right, lines
are prepped, you excited?

28:24.329 --> 28:26.122
Yeah, a little bit nervous.

28:26.164 --> 28:28.208
So, you can always have him come
over, and you can both do those.

28:28.249 --> 28:30.085
Of course.

28:30.126 --> 28:32.045
It's a little nerve-wracking,
docking as a new team,

28:32.087 --> 28:34.297
especially with
the size of the boat.

28:34.339 --> 28:37.092
One little mistake can
lead into a bigger one.

28:37.133 --> 28:38.593
Just take off, yeah, the top,

28:38.635 --> 28:40.011
and then just leave
similar to this one.

28:40.053 --> 28:41.596
All right, starboard forward.

28:41.638 --> 28:44.307
Oh, my God, love these.

28:46.267 --> 28:47.644
You can free up the line.

28:47.686 --> 28:49.396
Copy.

28:49.437 --> 28:50.939
Go, go.

28:50.980 --> 28:53.149
That is your two cross-backs
coming off now.

28:53.191 --> 28:54.359
All lines off.

28:54.401 --> 28:56.361
We can release this one,
go, go, go.

28:56.403 --> 28:59.322
That is all stern lines on deck.

28:59.364 --> 29:01.408
We're off, we're moving.

29:03.243 --> 29:06.121
Forty feet starboard midships
to dock,

29:06.162 --> 29:07.455
all clear off
your stern to swing.

29:07.497 --> 29:08.540
<i>Thank you, nice work.</i>

29:08.581 --> 29:10.917
[bleep] yeah, Z.

29:10.959 --> 29:13.044
You did it, boy.

29:13.086 --> 29:14.212
Go down for two hours.

29:14.254 --> 29:16.047
-Thank you.
-Pleasure.

29:16.089 --> 29:19.050
So, we've got a lentil and
octopus salad, quinoa salad.

29:19.092 --> 29:20.927
-Oh, beautiful!
-Mm!

29:20.969 --> 29:25.056
Some fresh chicken, we have some
falafels and a tzaziki sauce,

29:25.098 --> 29:27.267
and then we have a burrata
and heirloom salad.

29:27.308 --> 29:29.102
So, this is gonna be
the best lunch we have.

29:30.270 --> 29:31.479
Delicious.

29:31.521 --> 29:33.398
Mm, this is perfect...
light, filling.

29:33.440 --> 29:35.608
So, who's gonna cook for us?

29:35.650 --> 29:37.527
I think that's...
I think this one...

29:37.569 --> 29:39.571
I actually think this is mine
and that one's his.

29:39.612 --> 29:41.072
I did, like, cocktail
service at home,

29:41.114 --> 29:42.741
and one of my captain
friends was, like,

29:42.782 --> 29:45.535
how about you work on this
boat for me in Exuma?

29:45.577 --> 29:47.078
It was good money,
I'm on a yacht.

29:47.120 --> 29:48.663
I mean, can't hate that.

29:48.705 --> 29:50.957
But I really prefer
the days where someone

29:50.999 --> 29:53.418
handed me the champagne,
so yeah.

29:53.460 --> 29:54.419
They're gonna get a chef.

29:54.461 --> 29:55.462
Okay.

29:57.464 --> 29:59.341
Do you wanna help me
drop the anchors today?

29:59.382 --> 30:00.592
Yeah.

30:00.633 --> 30:02.093
You would wait for
her to tell you,

30:02.135 --> 30:03.094
or you would say
"ready at the anchor."

30:03.136 --> 30:04.596
You ask.

30:04.637 --> 30:06.014
When she says,
"Drop, drop, drop," let 'er rip.

30:06.056 --> 30:07.974
Being back here on the
Dalmatian Coast,

30:08.016 --> 30:09.434
based in Sibenik,

30:09.476 --> 30:12.270
it's more nature,
country, small village.

30:12.312 --> 30:13.271
I love that.

30:13.313 --> 30:14.314
How was lunch?

30:14.356 --> 30:15.607
The quinoa salad was bomb.

30:15.648 --> 30:16.733
It was great.

30:18.276 --> 30:19.319
-Yeah, of course.
-Thank you.

30:19.361 --> 30:20.695
-Two.
-Two espresso martinis?

30:20.737 --> 30:21.696
-Three.
-Same.

30:21.738 --> 30:22.781
Four?

30:22.822 --> 30:24.282
Just do a round for everybody.

30:26.659 --> 30:28.119
When I'm dealing
with demanding guests,

30:28.161 --> 30:30.789
I'm, like, a
pretty laid-back Kiwi.

30:30.830 --> 30:33.208
But sometimes I turn
into a stressed-out bitch,

30:33.249 --> 30:35.585
so, you know, whatever.
I'm not perfect.

30:35.627 --> 30:37.379
Hi.

30:37.420 --> 30:39.005
Yeah, we were told to put
some of the stuff in laundry?

30:39.047 --> 30:40.548
No, it wasn't in laundry,

30:40.590 --> 30:42.258
it just needs to be steamed,
everything's clean.

30:42.300 --> 30:43.426
But I have all my stuff
in there, so I need to change.

30:43.468 --> 30:45.095
Okay.

30:45.136 --> 30:46.429
I did already put some of it
in the washing machine,

30:46.471 --> 30:47.639
because she asked...

30:47.681 --> 30:49.265
Oh, nothing needs
to be washed...

30:49.307 --> 30:50.642
But okay, that's where
the confusion was.

30:50.684 --> 30:51.810
Anything that I haven't
put in bring up to you.

30:51.851 --> 30:54.479
-Okay.
-Okay.

30:54.521 --> 30:57.357
Oh, don't fly away!

31:02.195 --> 31:03.738
It's not been steamed!

31:13.623 --> 31:15.208
Let it go, drop the anchor.

31:15.250 --> 31:16.251
-You got it?
-Yeah.

31:16.292 --> 31:17.502
All right, I trust you.

31:17.544 --> 31:20.213
So, we have some
espresso martinis.

31:24.551 --> 31:27.303
Little more.

31:27.345 --> 31:28.430
That's good.

31:28.471 --> 31:29.723
Nice job, guys.

31:34.436 --> 31:36.521
I've only managed to
press these ones just so far.

31:36.563 --> 31:37.522
Thank you, Courtney.

31:37.564 --> 31:39.107
No problem.

31:39.149 --> 31:41.609
We have the rest of
the espresso martinis.

31:41.651 --> 31:44.195
Thank you.

31:44.237 --> 31:45.655
Oh, yeah, okay,
I heard about this.

31:45.697 --> 31:49.409
So, I'm gonna task you
with 100 glow sticks.

31:49.451 --> 31:51.661
Okay.

31:51.703 --> 31:53.413
These are like glasses
and all the things

31:53.455 --> 31:54.414
-that they made.
-Okay.

31:54.456 --> 31:56.207
Okay.

31:56.249 --> 31:57.208
So, I'm gonna hand those
to y'all for later tonight.

31:57.250 --> 31:58.251
Sure.

32:02.172 --> 32:03.381
There she is.

32:03.423 --> 32:04.841
Excuse me, no pictures,
please.

32:04.883 --> 32:06.176
Look at this beautifulness,
oh, my God.

32:06.217 --> 32:07.719
Ooh, is that a cave right there?

32:07.761 --> 32:10.347
Like, if you were Batman,
you would want that cave.

32:12.432 --> 32:14.225
Keep pulling.

32:20.398 --> 32:22.859
Okay, David's gonna
be your slide man.

32:22.901 --> 32:24.277
Who's first?

32:24.319 --> 32:25.737
-Go, Terez, go!
-All right.

32:25.779 --> 32:27.489
Ah!

32:39.626 --> 32:40.919
We have another vessel
in the marina

32:40.960 --> 32:42.504
that's quarantined
in the bubble,

32:42.545 --> 32:44.631
and I've asked for their
sous chef to come help.

32:44.673 --> 32:46.591
She's not a chef,
but she's a sous chef,

32:46.633 --> 32:48.843
so we're gonna figure
this out together.

32:48.885 --> 32:51.304
-Woo!
-Ah!

32:56.810 --> 32:57.811
[bleep]

32:57.852 --> 32:58.812
I might head up
to the hot tub.

32:58.853 --> 33:00.355
-Okay.
-Cool.

33:00.397 --> 33:02.273
All right, well, yeah,
enjoy the hot tub.

33:02.315 --> 33:05.485
<i>All crew, meet me in the crew</i>
<i>mess for a quick meeting.</i>

33:08.655 --> 33:11.408
I have a feeling Chef
is not coming back.

33:12.826 --> 33:16.621
So, we have a chef
that can help in the galley,

33:16.663 --> 33:19.165
but we need to make dinner.

33:23.003 --> 33:24.796
So, we could do
surf-and-turf, right?

33:24.838 --> 33:26.589
Someone could grab the oysters
and the lobster

33:26.631 --> 33:28.925
and bring them up to the galley,
we could start that.

33:28.967 --> 33:30.218
-Okay.
-...grab them.

33:30.260 --> 33:31.511
We'll look.

33:31.553 --> 33:32.679
You'll be in the galley
to start now?

33:32.721 --> 33:33.722
-Yep.
-Okay.

33:33.763 --> 33:35.807
Good job.

33:35.849 --> 33:37.308
We're ----ed.

33:37.350 --> 33:38.810
Okay, let's go
to the main salon,

33:38.852 --> 33:40.478
let's finish pulling
the rest of this.

33:40.520 --> 33:41.813
What do you want,
lobster and lamb?

33:41.855 --> 33:42.814
Did you say crabs?

33:42.856 --> 33:43.815
Oh, I don't want crabs.

33:43.857 --> 33:45.442
[laughing]

33:45.483 --> 33:46.860
We're gonna pack
that slide away.

33:48.528 --> 33:49.779
Yeah.

33:49.821 --> 33:52.282
Okay, let's pour
the oysters in here.

33:52.323 --> 33:53.533
Sweet.

33:55.994 --> 33:57.537
Oh, hello, boys.

33:57.579 --> 33:58.747
I'm not really a pro on lobster.

33:58.788 --> 34:00.457
Google it.

34:00.498 --> 34:01.624
Do you guys like a later dinner?

34:01.666 --> 34:03.501
We can do, like, 8:30.

34:03.543 --> 34:05.211
I'll tell you what,
we are not cooking.

34:05.253 --> 34:07.380
-Woohoo!
-We trust you guys.

34:07.422 --> 34:10.425
I've never eaten them like this.

34:10.467 --> 34:12.635
Oh!

34:12.677 --> 34:14.512
I'm not really,
like, a hunting type.

34:14.554 --> 34:16.848
Back home, I don't shoot
rabbits or nothing.

34:16.890 --> 34:18.391
There's no way I could do that.

34:18.433 --> 34:21.519
I should not be in here.
What am I doing in here?

34:21.561 --> 34:22.896
I can do them.

34:22.937 --> 34:26.816
How do you kindly
kill a lobster?

34:26.858 --> 34:27.859
Sh--.

34:27.901 --> 34:29.903
<i>Plunge a sharp knife...</i>

34:31.571 --> 34:33.656
Oh! Savage!

34:41.706 --> 34:42.082
Oh, savage.

34:43.833 --> 34:46.378
Seems like they're scrambling
without having a chef.

34:46.419 --> 34:47.587
Oh!

34:47.629 --> 34:48.797
Hi.

34:52.384 --> 34:54.302
-Okay.
-Yeah.

34:54.344 --> 34:56.012
Oh, that's probably the worst
I've ever felt about myself.

34:56.054 --> 34:57.430
Captain Sandy?

34:57.472 --> 34:58.431
Yeah, I'm here.

34:58.473 --> 34:59.557
Hello, Duska.

34:59.599 --> 35:00.600
Welcome, nice to meet you.

35:00.642 --> 35:02.394
Nice to meet you too, yes.

35:02.435 --> 35:05.939
So, we've got lobster,
the steaks, and the oysters.

35:05.980 --> 35:07.482
Lobsters...

35:08.817 --> 35:10.318
You know nothing?

35:12.445 --> 35:14.322
Oh, okay.

35:15.824 --> 35:17.951
-Okay.
-Okay.

35:17.992 --> 35:19.452
I put me heart and soul
into just murdering

35:19.494 --> 35:21.329
all these ----ing lobsters,

35:21.371 --> 35:24.624
and then the chef turns up
and she can't cook lobsters.

35:24.666 --> 35:26.042
The [bleep]?

35:35.927 --> 35:37.512
-Yes.
-Okay.

35:37.554 --> 35:39.806
All right, buddy, I'm sorry.

35:39.848 --> 35:42.684
Whew, are we loving charter?

35:42.726 --> 35:44.519
Ah! [bleep]

35:45.729 --> 35:47.063
Nice.

35:47.105 --> 35:48.732
So not fair.

35:51.568 --> 35:53.403
Coming down... good.

35:53.445 --> 35:54.446
Copy.

35:54.487 --> 35:55.697
I'm lined up.

36:01.453 --> 36:02.954
Oh, my God, was he alive?

36:02.996 --> 36:03.997
Yeah, they all are.

36:04.039 --> 36:05.081
Yeah, it's very fresh.

36:05.123 --> 36:06.791
They're fresh.

36:06.833 --> 36:08.376
Really?

36:08.418 --> 36:09.919
-We need way more stuff.
-That's pretty.

36:09.961 --> 36:11.921
Just... no, that is fine,
just like that.

36:11.963 --> 36:13.173
I know, but we need...

36:13.214 --> 36:14.174
We're gonna hang these, yeah.

36:14.215 --> 36:16.009
Who even likes neon?

36:16.051 --> 36:18.595
I come from working on
pretty high-end boats.

36:18.636 --> 36:21.681
Everything is meant to be
really, like, nice and elegant,

36:21.723 --> 36:24.726
and I don't do
tacky table décor.

36:24.768 --> 36:27.729
So, neon theme hurts
my soul a little bit.

36:28.730 --> 36:29.939
Ooh.

36:31.566 --> 36:33.902
Nice, all right,
that's good, thank you.

36:33.943 --> 36:35.570
Let's go get ready for dinner.

36:35.612 --> 36:37.197
Birthday party!

36:37.238 --> 36:39.074
Oh, my God, they're
popping open, I'm so happy.

36:39.115 --> 36:40.617
Are they aphrodisiac?

36:40.658 --> 36:41.910
Yes.

36:45.747 --> 36:47.540
Tacky, tacky, tacky.

36:47.582 --> 36:49.042
I think we should try
to cook one of those,

36:49.084 --> 36:50.460
to see how it tastes.

36:50.502 --> 36:52.170
Yeah.
This is not okay.

36:52.212 --> 36:54.881
I'm just in there doing
what I'm, like, I don't know...

36:54.923 --> 36:57.133
making ----ing sh-- I used
to make for the family

36:57.175 --> 36:58.718
that I used to nanny for.

36:58.760 --> 37:00.804
Onions and tomatoes together,

37:00.845 --> 37:01.888
like, pan-fried,
and then, like...

37:01.930 --> 37:04.849
Yeah, like salad.

37:04.891 --> 37:06.726
-Like a salad?
-In a salad.

37:06.768 --> 37:10.105
And then Duska's there,
like, no idea what's going on.

37:10.146 --> 37:12.065
Oh, I'm not doing
so well over here.

37:12.107 --> 37:14.651
[bleep] it's hot!

37:14.693 --> 37:16.611
Yeah, I could do a salad,
that's probably a better idea.

37:16.653 --> 37:18.738
Salad.

37:18.780 --> 37:21.574
I'm not having success
on the lobster.

37:21.616 --> 37:24.828
What's happening in the galley
right now is a disaster.

37:24.869 --> 37:27.038
Worst-case scenario,
we'll make 'em paninis.

37:27.080 --> 37:29.582
Well done today, guys.

37:29.624 --> 37:33.003
Lloyd, in that hat, you
look like Mario.

37:34.713 --> 37:36.923
[humming]

37:40.802 --> 37:42.679
It's me, Mario!

37:42.721 --> 37:44.639
No?

37:44.681 --> 37:48.727
So, you two in epaulettes,
you're adios.

37:48.768 --> 37:50.603
All right.

37:50.645 --> 37:52.522
I don't know what to do.

37:52.564 --> 37:54.274
Okay, just to go over exactly
what we're having tonight,

37:54.315 --> 37:55.859
so we've got lobster tails?

37:55.900 --> 37:56.943
Yeah...

37:56.985 --> 37:58.528
Maybe.

37:58.570 --> 38:00.196
Maybe, we don't really... yeah.

38:00.238 --> 38:02.699
Steak, roasted veg,
and oysters.

38:04.117 --> 38:06.703
Is the Captain really cooking?

38:06.745 --> 38:07.787
You manning the grill?

38:07.829 --> 38:09.122
Yeah, well, I'm gonna try it.

38:09.164 --> 38:10.790
You got no room for error.

38:10.832 --> 38:12.751
I literally haven't peed
in, like, five hours.

38:12.792 --> 38:14.127
Ugh.

38:17.213 --> 38:18.882
Sorry.

38:18.923 --> 38:21.509
Malia, can you just confirm
what my uniform will be?

38:29.309 --> 38:30.643
